In Realm #1 space -infinite amounts, + empty- reappears, but not time. + in each higher realm not only does multiplicity decrease but also change. Until you wind up with infinite space (the Abyss) + no change, i.e. no time. Apparently realms #3 + #2 are conceptual but realm #1 -the One- is not. Nous exists in #2, not #1. Nous (#2) is the One become self-aware + hence split (I think). Anyhow it is differentiated, but still unified (Valis). E of Ph on Plotinus: "According to Aristotle, Plato had assumed a realm of Mathematicals mediating between ideas [Form world] + sensibles [accidents world] - a doctrine Aristotle related to a similar, equally dualistic doctrine of the Pythagoreans." I saw this realm: Esp. the .618034 doorway which must have led from our spatiotemporal accidental realm to the Form realm, + that doorway was closing + I could no longer see the upper realm after that. "Aristotle designated the supreme deity as Intelligence (Nous) contemplating itself." "Plotinus subdivided Plato's realm of intelligibles into 3: the One, Intelligence (Nous) + the Soul "Plotinus tries to show that just because Intelligence + Soul are not extended, they can be omnipresent + ubiquitous in what is extended" [the spatiotemporal realm]. "The most striking example of the real effects of the Soul's falling away from Intelligence is that the cosmic soul, as it falls away, engenders time because of an inability to contemplate the totality of Intelligence simultaneously."

